The SQL file already has it. Just paste the whole updated `galaxy_gravity.sql` into the Supabase SQL Editor and hit Run. The relevant lines are:

```sql
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS public.get_universe_posts_viewport;
CREATE FUNCTION public.get_universe_posts_viewport(...);

DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS public.find_similar_post_pairs;
CREATE FUNCTION public.find_similar_post_pairs(...);

DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS public.get_star_galaxy_pulls;
CREATE FUNCTION public.get_star_galaxy_pulls(...);
```

Supabase SQL Editor: **left sidebar > SQL Editor > New query > paste all > Run**. The `DROP IF EXISTS` deletes the old function (if it exists) so the `CREATE` with the new return type succeeds cleanly.

